docs.lead_paragraph: As to who were the first Jews that came to England, Mr. Jacobs does not trouble himself. We know that in the Liber Ruber of 1198 rules are laid down to Christian and Jew about the sale of tin from the Stannaries, and presumably Jews came to Cornwall with or after the Phenician, to buy tin.
